Britain's food safety watchdog Thursday added another 146 products to a list of items tainted by a potentially cancer-causing dye in the country's largest food recall yet.
EU fears food scare may spread; problem dye came from India
More foods added to Britain's cancer food dye recall list
Sudan I, a potentially cancer-causing colorant, is the latest target for China's product qualitywatchdogs after the disclosure that the red dye has tainted hundreds of food items in Britain, Thursday's China Daily reported.
